+## 2026-07-10
+
+- [x] **`--sessions` auto-resume survives the out-of-credits block (heartbeat watchdog)** — task_016. Empirically (3 overnight instances) interactive claude does NOT exit when a Pro/Max usage window is exhausted; it blocks forever at the interactive usage-limit picker, so the existing relaunch loop never ran. Fix: `settings.local.json`'s heredoc gains PreToolUse/PostToolUse/Stop hook entries (matcher `""`) that atomically write an epoch to `.vss/heartbeat` while a `/vsss --sessions` marker exists; `launch_claude`'s body becomes `exec devcontainer exec ...` so a new `launch_claude_supervised` can background it, capture the real client PID, and run a `vibe_stall_watchdog` alongside it. The watchdog's kill gate is three conditions, all required — marker `active=1` (not `pending`, so the final window stays protected), the marker refreshed during THIS launcher session (portable `[ marker -nt ref ]` against a new session-start `VIBE_SESSION_REF`, with the relaunch call sites arming unconditionally via the literal sentinel `-`, and an empty ref from a mktemp failure never arming), and a stale heartbeat (`auto_resume_stalled`, default 1800s) — so a crash-left marker can never trigger a kill against an unrelated later interactive session. On trigger: warn, grace period, re-check, in-container kill (`vibe_container_kill_claude`, a literal bare `devcontainer exec ... pkill -TERM -x claude`) then host-PID fallback. Two hardening additions: a per-iteration `INT` trap in the countdown loop deactivates the marker on Ctrl-C (cancel means cancel) without touching the EXIT slot (the clipboard-watcher trap is untouched); and claude's exit status is now captured in `CLAUDE_EXIT` and propagated as vibe's own final exit code, replacing the old `|| true` swallow. New helpers (`auto_resume_deactivate`, `auto_resume_heartbeat_write`, `auto_resume_stalled`, `vibe_container_kill_claude`, `vibe_stall_watchdog`, `_vibe_stall_armed`) all live before the `VIBE_SOURCE_ONLY` guard for unit-testability. `.gitignore` gains `.vss/heartbeat*`; `MANUAL-TESTS.md` gains Test 32 (six sub-cases); `devcontainer/commands/vsss.md` § Auto-resume documents the launcher-side watchdog contract and why the skill's existing per-iteration marker refresh is now load-bearing. shellcheck clean (15 files); smoke suite green, 1000/1000 checks, no regressions.
+
 ## 2026-07-08
 
 - [x] **`/vsss --auto-resume N` renamed `--sessions X`** — Martin's call: the old flag was unmemorable. New semantics are the intuitive ones: X = TOTAL credit windows (`--sessions 3` = current window + up to 2 relaunches; `--sessions 1` = no relaunch), so the marker's `remaining` = X-1. The old flag counted EXTRA windows; the spec tells any future reader to treat a stray `--auto-resume N` as `--sessions N+1`. The `.vss/auto-resume` marker file, its KEY=VALUE format and the launcher's `auto_resume_*` helpers are all unchanged — the launcher never sees the flag, only the marker, so no launcher logic moved. vsss.md + README updated; smoke checks assert the new flag name and the X-1 arithmetic are documented.
